parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or slip out of gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Clutch system failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front axle/CV joint failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: CV joints need to be replaced multiple times

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Shift pattern indicator/linkage failure can cause confusion or loss of control while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Speedometer failure can cause the driver to lose track of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
Transfer case failure can cause loss of power or control in 4-wheel drive vehicles, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the brake pedal to engage properly can cause extended stopping distances, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor with no braking effect
the brake pedal does not engage until almost to the floor
the brake pedal makes a loud noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake rotors and pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Excessive wear on brake rotors and pads
frequent replacements of brake rotors and pads
loud grinding noise when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration and noise when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: loud noise when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
Brake failure can lead to accidents, causing damage to the vehicle and potentially injuring occupants.
symptoms: brake pedal going to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shutting down of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down without warning
and may be accompanied by a burning smell or excessive fuel consumption.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause engine damage, overheating, and fires, leading to accidents, injuries, or vehicle destruction.
symptoms: causing fluid to leak into the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause engine stalling, loss of control, and accidents, as well as fires and injuries.
symptoms: The wiring harness melts or overheats
and may be accompanied by transmission slipping out of gear and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emissions system can cause engine performance issues, excessive fuel consumption, and environmental pollution.
symptoms: The exhaust gas recirculation valve fails
and the check engine light illuminates periodically
accompanied by excessive fuel consumption and a burning smell.
